    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-12-04T07:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-12-04T07:00:00-05:00" n="536"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d536">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">D. H. Miller</persName> to Colonel
                            <persName type="to">E. M. House</persName>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="20" type="source" xml:id="d536fn20">This telegram is reprinted from
                        Miller, <hi rend="italic">My Diary</hi>, vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">i</hi>,
                        p. 30.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-12-04T12:00:00+00:00"
                            >December 4, 1918—noon</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I am informed that at yesterday’s meeting of Premiers note of President regarding
                        relief<note n="21" xml:id="d536fn21">See <hi rend="italic">supra.</hi>
                    </note> was referred to a committee names of whom I do not know and that this
                    means postponement of question until President’s arrival.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>[<hi rend="smallcaps">D. H. Miller</hi>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
